    "created_at": "2012-03-26T22:21:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-03-26T22:21:11Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I could even see a 'Close and halt' entry in the File menu, which stops the kernel and closes the window.  I won't push that this needs to be configurable, only that there needs to be _some_ way for close&term to be a single action, whether it's a configurable flag for window-closing behavior or a separately selectable action is inconsequential to me.\n\nLong-term, I probably see this as an admin-panel option of idle-timeout, where the server shuts down kernels that are not in use after a period of time.  This could easily be infinite by default, but I think most users would not expect their kernel  state to have been preserved if they open a notebook that has been closed for an hour or more.\n"
  },
