    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, I do think we want an explicit close and halt button from within\nthe notebook as well.  Can you close a Browser window from javascript?\n Might be blocked by popup blocker logic.  Will have to look into\nthat.\n\nOn Mon, Mar 26, 2012 at 3:21 PM, Min RK\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> I could even see a 'Close and halt' entry in the File menu, which stops the kernel and closes the window.  I won't push that this needs to be configurable, only that there needs to be _some_ way for close&term to be a single action, whether it's a configurable flag for window-closing behavior or a separately selectable action is inconsequential to me.\n> \n> Long-term, I probably see this as an admin-panel option of idle-timeout, where the server shuts down kernels that are not in use after a period of time.  This could easily be infinite by default, but I think most users would not expect their kernel  state to have been preserved if they open a notebook that has been closed for an hour or more.\n\nYes, I think this makes sense as well.\n\n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1515#issuecomment-4705698\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
